    <section>
        <h4 id="how-to-combat-this">How to combat this</h4>
        <p>To combat this, try not sharing alot of your art or code online, or slap a license on it. Many platforms let you disable the feeding of your content into AI via settings. Most notable include Github, Youtube, and more. Most AI companies are not allowed to take your content if it has a license or is copyrighted. For example, Sora once had a strike because it used copyrighted content like &quot;<em>Sponge Bob</em>&quot; and &quot;<em>Mario</em>&quot;, which was banned later on the app so you couldn&#39;t make videos with them in it.</p>
        <p>If you were an AI heavy person that is trying to not use AI again, Try desintegrating AI a little bit every day.</p>
        <br>
        <p>For example:</p>
        <p>Learning art one day, and the next day using Google sites (a relatively easy site maker) to make a website yourself.</p>
